DATA CLOUD
Data Foundation Solution Workflow

Review the solution workflow for integrating your initial data foundation in Marketing Cloud Engagement.

ESTABLISH DATA FOUNDATION REQUIREMENTS FOR MARKETING CLOUD
ENGAGEMENT	CREATE CORE ACTIVATIONS IN DATA CLOUD	LINK CORE ACTIVATIONS TO THE MARKETING CLOUD ENGAGEMENT CONTACT MODEL	USE DATA FROM DATA CLOUD THROUGHOUT MARKETING CLOUD
ENGAGEMENT

Identify common content personalization and decisioning attributes used in Journey Builder
Determine if you’re implementing a Core Audience Model or a Collective Core Audience Model
	
Create a segment that represents your full audience in Data Cloud
Create Data Cloud activations of your full audience to Marketing Cloud Engagement
Activate commonly used personalization and decisioning attributes
	
Create Contact Model attribute groups in Marketing Cloud Engagement for each Data Cloud activation grouping
Link the activated data extensions to the applicable Contact Model attribute group in Marketing Cloud Engagement
Create one additional Contact Model attribute group in Marketing Cloud Engagement for ad hoc campaigns
	
Audience-based journeys (data extensions for journey entry)
Event-triggered journeys (API-triggered journey entry)
